<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[192,1440,742,868]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,303,742,768]" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
The only specimen of this species was captured by beating on broad-leaved shrubs in a shady subtropical rainforest in Western 
<collectingRegion box="[471,561,776,802]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Yunnan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[572,644,775,801]" name="China" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">China</collectingCountry>
. Because the appearance of this species is so similar to some 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brulle" authorityYear="1834" box="[1317,1440,775,801]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Collyridini">Collyridini</taxonomicName>
species, especially genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Horn" authorityYear="1901" box="[475,593,809,835]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Neocollyris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[475,593,809,835]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="4">Neocollyris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which can also be found in the same habitat, it may be part of a mimicry complex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
